            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document and standardise the process for recording patient referrals that are on the ASI work list in e-Referral Service (eRS) manually in Lorenzo EPR."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document and standardise the process for tracking and updating the patient's pathway status to ensure accurate RTT information is recorded"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Provide a baseline for future process improvements"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Assist in developing baseline for the development of training material"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Please refer to the OPD01 \u2013 Outpatients: Referral Management and Access Planning for a detailed description of end to end outpatient procedure."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Overview"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "This process outlines how to manually record patient referrals that are \u201cDeferred to Provider\u201d on"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "eRS i.e. when appointment slots are not available on Lorenzo EPR for eRS referrals to be booked in to. These referrals will fall on the ASI worklist in eRS and they should be managed by the Referral Booking Management System (RBMS) and the relevant service (i.e. where the service manages their referrals)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Please note -"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "All referral documentation must be downloaded from E-RS to be saved in the patient's record in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Additional guidance"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Prior to adding a new referral to a patient's record, the user must review the active referrals in the referrals tab of patients EPR in Lorenzo, to see if the patient has an active referral in the same service. If this is the case then a new referral must not be created as this will start a new pathway in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Staff must escalate referrals that have incomplete details to their supervisor or team leader before this can be added to Lorenzo EPR."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Role \u2013 RBMS Booking Clerk / Booking Clerk"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Specific Procedure- Record referrals on the ASI worklist in Lorenzo EPR"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Steps in Lorenzo"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 2,
                "num_cols": 2,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Lorenzo Field"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Value to be Selected"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Service type requested"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Will default to Advice/Consultation - Leave with default selection."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 28,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 14,
                "num_cols": 1,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Referral priority"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Select Routine / 2 week wait or fast track / urgent as per the referral from the set of drop down values"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referral type"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Select Outpatient"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referral source"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Select General Medical Practitioner for GP referrals."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Admin category"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "This will default to NHS Patient. Any private patient activity will require the user to change this to Private patient from the drop down list."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referral action"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Select Record Referral"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referral media"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Select Choose and Book"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Suspected cancer site"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "This field will become active when referral priority = 2WW and referral source = General Medical Practitioner"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referred By Section"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Organisation / Care provider"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "The GP details will auto populate."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referral create date/time"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "This is the date the referral was created by the GP. User should check the referral history in eRS to see when the patient was originally referred to see when the referral was created."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referral received date/time"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "This date is when the referral falls on the ASI worklist. The user must check the referral history in eRS for this date. This can be found when the user clicks the UBRN icon in eRS, as this shows the referral history. Please note that the received date triggers the start of a patient's 18 week pathway in Lorenzo EPR. In the case where the appointment has been cancelled, the actual received date will also be in the referral history."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Comments"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Record relevant information e.g. ASI referral from eRS or deferred from eRS"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referred to Section \u2013 Complete as appropriate"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Referred to type"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Select Team for general referrals to a service or Care provider for referrals that specifically must be graded by an individual care provider. Please note: All referrals via the RBMS must be referred to a \u201cTeam\u201d The Specialty and Treatment function will pre-populate when a care provider or Team is searched and selected."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "This screen holds the details for RTT monitoring, the referral details from the previous screen is pre- populated. However the user must complete the other fields as listed below. This will ensure that the correct RTT pathway is recorded."
            }
        },
